The paper is about optimizing neural network architectures for deep learning, which is a core topic in machine learning. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also involves automated methods for finding neural network architectures, which falls under the category of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). The experiments in the paper involve image classification tasks, which are commonly studied in the Computer Vision (cs.CV) category. The use of Monte Carlo planning and UCT algorithms also suggests a connection to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) category. Finally, the paper proposes a practical method for deep learning architecture optimization, which could be relevant to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) category.
